layers = fiona.listlayers(workspace)
for layer in layers:
    gdf = gpd.read_file(workspace, layer=layer)
    print(gdf.crs)
    print(len(gdf))
    print(gdf.geom_type.unique())
    print(f'list{(gdf.columns)}\n')
    gdf.plot()
    plt.title(f"{layer}")
    plt.show()

In [25]:
def explore_gdb(workspace= None):
    layers = fiona.listlayers(workspace)
    for layer in layers:
        gdf = gpd.read_file(workspace, layer=layer)
        print(gdf.crs)
        print(len(gdf))
        print(gdf.geom_type.unique())
        print(f'list{(gdf.columns)}\n')
        gdf.plot()
        plt.title(f"{layer}")
        plt.show()
